      It‚Äôs time to roll out your yoga mat and discover the combination of
      physical and mental exercises that for thousands of years have hooked yoga
      practitioners around the globe. The beauty of yoga is that you don‚Äôt have
      to be a yogi or yogini to reap the benefits. Whether you are young or old,
      overweight or fit, yoga has the power to calm the mind and strengthen the
      body. Don‚Äôt be intimidated by yoga terminology, fancy yoga studios and
      complicated poses. Yoga is for <em>everyone</em> . <br /><br />

      <strong>Why 30 days?</strong> <br /><br />

      Did you know that research actually shows that a new habit takes around 66
      days to develop? So a 66 day yoga challenge would be perfect if you‚Äôre
      determined to solidify an everyday practice. However, it could be so long
      that it seems daunting and unattainable. I think a 30 day yoga challenge
      is the perfect inbetween - committing to a month of yoga seems doable in
      my eyes, and the progress you see along the way will be sure to keep you
      motivated! Plus, you can do several 30 day challenges if you‚Äôre really
      wanting to develop that habit!

